Grammy winner Wizkid has announced the postponement of his Made In Lagos tour in Canada as a result of coronavirus. Wizkid made this known on Wednesday in one of his Instagram stories saying he will no longer perform for his yearning Canadian fans due to some restrictions due to COVID-19. “Due to the existing and developing public health restriction measures being introduced by the Canadian government, I will no longer be able to perform my Canadian shows in January 2022,” he began.   Davido continues ballistic attack on cousin over Osun Gov…     I was depressed but lived in denial – Toyin Abraham     Engagement added to my glow – Seyi Shay   He, however, promised to return to Canada for the tour, which was originally scheduled to start in January 2022. - Advertisement - “I’m looking forward to returning as soon as possible,” he said. Wizkid’s Made In Lagos tour in the United States of America and the United Kingdom are still being talked about as he sold out tickets and had top music stars like Rihanna, Draka and more attend some of his concerts during the tour.